<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="584" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,719,2005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1044,1069]" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This apterous new species has female subgenital plate transverse and forming two parts: a small anterior lobe and a large posterior plate; anterior part forming a lobe, wider than long, broadly, deeply, and roundly emarginated with two lateral lobules; lobule with rounded apex; posterior part broadly triangular, with apex subacute. Male subgenital plate with posterior margin broadly emarginate, laterally forming a lobe where stylus is inserted. In both males and females, the new species has four stridulatory files on first and second tergites, with circa 5 (most anterior), 14, 15, and 18 (most posterior) teeth respectively.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,719,2005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1260,1285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">Comparison.</emphasis>
The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Karny" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[732,896,1260,1284]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllacrididae" genus="Melaneremus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borneensis">
<emphasis box="[732,896,1260,1284]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">M. borneensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by shape of female subgenital plate; shorter ovipositor (15.8 
<emphasis box="[342,373,1297,1320]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">vs.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[382,489,1296,1320]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.92" pageId="5" pageNumber="584" unit="mm" value="19.2">19.2 mm</quantity>
), barely longer than posterior femur; male ninth abdominal tergite with distal part without median vertical furrow. It also differs from other Southeast Asian species: subapterous 
<taxonomicName authority="(Karny, 1924)" authorityName="Karny" authorityYear="1924" baseAuthorityName="Karny" baseAuthorityYear="1924" class="Insecta" family="Gryllacrididae" genus="Melaneremus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="javanicus">
<emphasis box="[1286,1436,1333,1356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">M. javanicus</emphasis>
(Karny, 1924)
</taxonomicName>
(not trapezoidal with posterior margin emarginated) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Karny, 1937" authorityName="Karny" authorityYear="1937" box="[944,1257,1368,1392]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllacrididae" genus="Melaneremus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="larnacoides">
<emphasis box="[944,1113,1368,1392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">M. larnacoides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[1120,1257,1368,1392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="584" refId="ref6195" refString="Karny, H. H. (1937) Orthoptera Fam. Gryllacrididae, Subfamiliae Omnes. Genera Insectorum, 206, 1 - 317." type="journal article">Karny, 1937</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(not truncated). Male tenth abdominal tergite also differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Griffini, 1913)" authorityName="Griffini" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Griffini" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[675,1005,1404,1429]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllacrididae" genus="Melaneremus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jacobsoni">
<emphasis box="[675,821,1404,1428]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">M. jacobsoni</emphasis>
(Griffini, 1913)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="587" pageId="5" pageNumber="584" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,719,2005]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="585" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,554,1439,1464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">
Description. Female 
<typeStatus box="[444,549,1439,1464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Habitus as shown in 
<figureCitation box="[791,857,1439,1464]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1544,1566]" captionTargetBox="[212,1374,324,1526]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[212,1374,324,1526]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Melaneremus? bellus sp. nov.: a female with nuptial gift (A), males (B, C), and a mating pair (D)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441901/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
. Head not enlarged, barely wider than the pronotum width (
<figureCitation box="[234,328,1476,1501]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Melaneremus? bellus sp. nov.: head and pronotum in dorsal view (A); face in anterior view (B); anterior half of body in lateral view (C); stridulatory files on abdominal tergite (D); female abdominal apex in posterior view (E); ovipositor in lateral view (F); female subgenital plate in ventral view (G); male abdominal apex in dorsal view (H); and male abdominal apex in ventral view (I). Scale bars: 5 mm (C, F); 2 mm (A, B, H); 1 mm (D, E, G, I)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441903/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
), with length circa 0.3 times of pronotum length. Vertex of fastigium slightly raised with apex truncated, circa twice the width of antennal scapus (
<figureCitation box="[743,893,1511,1536]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Melaneremus? bellus sp. nov.: head and pronotum in dorsal view (A); face in anterior view (B); anterior half of body in lateral view (C); stridulatory files on abdominal tergite (D); female abdominal apex in posterior view (E); ovipositor in lateral view (F); female subgenital plate in ventral view (G); male abdominal apex in dorsal view (H); and male abdominal apex in ventral view (I). Scale bars: 5 mm (C, F); 2 mm (A, B, H); 1 mm (D, E, G, I)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441903/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">Figs. 4A, 4B</figureCitation>
). Eye black, oval and prominent, with length in anterior view slightly longer than (1.2 times) length of scapus, and width in anterior view slightly shorter than (0.8 times) length of scapus; median ocellus very small, same height as the lower margin of antennal groove 
<figureCitation box="[1335,1423,1583,1608]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Melaneremus? bellus sp. nov.: head and pronotum in dorsal view (A); face in anterior view (B); anterior half of body in lateral view (C); stridulatory files on abdominal tergite (D); female abdominal apex in posterior view (E); ovipositor in lateral view (F); female subgenital plate in ventral view (G); male abdominal apex in dorsal view (H); and male abdominal apex in ventral view (I). Scale bars: 5 mm (C, F); 2 mm (A, B, H); 1 mm (D, E, G, I)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441903/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). Frons smooth (
<figureCitation box="[319,407,1620,1645]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Melaneremus? bellus sp. nov.: head and pronotum in dorsal view (A); face in anterior view (B); anterior half of body in lateral view (C); stridulatory files on abdominal tergite (D); female abdominal apex in posterior view (E); ovipositor in lateral view (F); female subgenital plate in ventral view (G); male abdominal apex in dorsal view (H); and male abdominal apex in ventral view (I). Scale bars: 5 mm (C, F); 2 mm (A, B, H); 1 mm (D, E, G, I)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441903/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
); labrum ovoid, longer than wide, ventral margin slightly emarginated. Maxillary palps long and slender, apical segment longer than subapical segment and third apical segment. Pronotum smooth, circa 1.2 times wider than long; disk with anterior margin feebly convex in the middle, with two very shallow oval depressions on each side of a faint longitudinal sulcus, smaller one on the anterior half, the other near posterior margin; posterior margin broadly emarginated (
<figureCitation box="[681,772,1764,1789]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Melaneremus? bellus sp. nov.: head and pronotum in dorsal view (A); face in anterior view (B); anterior half of body in lateral view (C); stridulatory files on abdominal tergite (D); female abdominal apex in posterior view (E); ovipositor in lateral view (F); female subgenital plate in ventral view (G); male abdominal apex in dorsal view (H); and male abdominal apex in ventral view (I). Scale bars: 5 mm (C, F); 2 mm (A, B, H); 1 mm (D, E, G, I)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441903/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
); dorsal lobe rounded into lateral lobe, surface smooth with sulcus barely visible, circa twice longer than deep, ventro-anterior angle broadly rounded, ventral margin almost straight, ventral angle truncated, broadly angular to posterior and ventral margins, and posterior margin nearly straight (
<figureCitation box="[260,358,1871,1896]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Melaneremus? bellus sp. nov.: head and pronotum in dorsal view (A); face in anterior view (B); anterior half of body in lateral view (C); stridulatory files on abdominal tergite (D); female abdominal apex in posterior view (E); ovipositor in lateral view (F); female subgenital plate in ventral view (G); male abdominal apex in dorsal view (H); and male abdominal apex in ventral view (I). Scale bars: 5 mm (C, F); 2 mm (A, B, H); 1 mm (D, E, G, I)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441903/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Mesonotum and metanotum transverse, posterior margin straight, with similar circular depression as pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[442,536,1908,1933]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Melaneremus? bellus sp. nov.: head and pronotum in dorsal view (A); face in anterior view (B); anterior half of body in lateral view (C); stridulatory files on abdominal tergite (D); female abdominal apex in posterior view (E); ovipositor in lateral view (F); female subgenital plate in ventral view (G); male abdominal apex in dorsal view (H); and male abdominal apex in ventral view (I). Scale bars: 5 mm (C, F); 2 mm (A, B, H); 1 mm (D, E, G, I)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441903/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Prosternum unarmed, but with two gently raised lobes, bearing a few setae. Mesosternal and metasternal lobes barely raised, but with a few long setae along margins. Apterous. Legs generally long and slender, with setae sparsely distributed. Anterior coxa with distinct but relatively stout and short spine. Anterior femur without spine, anterior tibia with 4–5 subapical ventral spurs on each margin; spurs with increasing size basally (
<figureCitation box="[301,393,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Melaneremus? bellus sp. nov.: head and pronotum in dorsal view (A); face in anterior view (B); anterior half of body in lateral view (C); stridulatory files on abdominal tergite (D); female abdominal apex in posterior view (E); ovipositor in lateral view (F); female subgenital plate in ventral view (G); male abdominal apex in dorsal view (H); and male abdominal apex in ventral view (I). Scale bars: 5 mm (C, F); 2 mm (A, B, H); 1 mm (D, E, G, I)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441903/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="585">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Middle femur also without spines, middle tibia with 4–5 subapical ventral spurs on each margin, the spurs with increasing size basally. Posterior femur with 7 stout subapical spines on outer margin, 10 on inner margin.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,1273,1544,1566]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441901/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="585" startId="6.[151,250,1544,1566]" targetBox="[212,1374,324,1526]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1273,1544,1566]" box="[151,1273,1544,1566]" pageId="6" pageNumber="585">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1544,1566]" pageId="6" pageNumber="585">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[281,497,1544,1566]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="585">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Karny" authorityYear="1937" box="[281,421,1544,1566]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllacrididae" genus="Melaneremus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="585" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Melaneremus</taxonomicName>
? bellus
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[503,584,1544,1565]" pageId="6" pageNumber="585">sp. nov.</emphasis>
: a female with nuptial gift (A), males (B, C), and a mating pair (D).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1610,2035]" pageId="6" pageNumber="585">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,291,1610,1635]" pageId="6" pageNumber="585">Female.</emphasis>
Four stridulatory files on first and second abdominal tergites, two on each tergite (
<figureCitation box="[1188,1276,1610,1635]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Melaneremus? bellus sp. nov.: head and pronotum in dorsal view (A); face in anterior view (B); anterior half of body in lateral view (C); stridulatory files on abdominal tergite (D); female abdominal apex in posterior view (E); ovipositor in lateral view (F); female subgenital plate in ventral view (G); male abdominal apex in dorsal view (H); and male abdominal apex in ventral view (I). Scale bars: 5 mm (C, F); 2 mm (A, B, H); 1 mm (D, E, G, I)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441903/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="585">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Anterior row on first tergite short with 5 peg-like teeth. Second file, also on first tergite, longer, more than twice the length of anterior file, slightly curved, with 14 peg-like teeth. Third file on second tergite curved, with 15 peg-like teeth; teeth more densely packed than second file; posterior file on second tergite nearly straight, with 18 peg-like teeth; teeth more densely packed than third file. Second to posterior files of subequal length. Eighth abdominal tergite reduced, shorter than anterior abdominal tergite; ninth abdominal tergite also reduced, but slightly longer than eighth abdominal tergite, tenth abdominal tergite reduced, deeply emarginated in the middle, forming lateral lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1424,1810,1835]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Melaneremus? bellus sp. nov.: head and pronotum in dorsal view (A); face in anterior view (B); anterior half of body in lateral view (C); stridulatory files on abdominal tergite (D); female abdominal apex in posterior view (E); ovipositor in lateral view (F); female subgenital plate in ventral view (G); male abdominal apex in dorsal view (H); and male abdominal apex in ventral view (I). Scale bars: 5 mm (C, F); 2 mm (A, B, H); 1 mm (D, E, G, I)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441903/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="585">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
). Epiproct small and tongue-shaped, depressed in the middle (
<figureCitation box="[830,917,1844,1869]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Melaneremus? bellus sp. nov.: head and pronotum in dorsal view (A); face in anterior view (B); anterior half of body in lateral view (C); stridulatory files on abdominal tergite (D); female abdominal apex in posterior view (E); ovipositor in lateral view (F); female subgenital plate in ventral view (G); male abdominal apex in dorsal view (H); and male abdominal apex in ventral view (I). Scale bars: 5 mm (C, F); 2 mm (A, B, H); 1 mm (D, E, G, I)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441903/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="585">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
). Cerci slender and short, tapering to an acute apex (
<figureCitation box="[217,302,1877,1902]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Melaneremus? bellus sp. nov.: head and pronotum in dorsal view (A); face in anterior view (B); anterior half of body in lateral view (C); stridulatory files on abdominal tergite (D); female abdominal apex in posterior view (E); ovipositor in lateral view (F); female subgenital plate in ventral view (G); male abdominal apex in dorsal view (H); and male abdominal apex in ventral view (I). Scale bars: 5 mm (C, F); 2 mm (A, B, H); 1 mm (D, E, G, I)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441903/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="585">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate transverse, much wider than long, forming two parts, a small anterior lobe and a large posterior plate (
<figureCitation box="[327,417,1910,1935]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Melaneremus? bellus sp. nov.: head and pronotum in dorsal view (A); face in anterior view (B); anterior half of body in lateral view (C); stridulatory files on abdominal tergite (D); female abdominal apex in posterior view (E); ovipositor in lateral view (F); female subgenital plate in ventral view (G); male abdominal apex in dorsal view (H); and male abdominal apex in ventral view (I). Scale bars: 5 mm (C, F); 2 mm (A, B, H); 1 mm (D, E, G, I)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441903/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="585">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
). Anterior part of subgenital plate forming a lobe, 0.6 times as wide as posterior part; lobe circa 2.4 times wider than long; broadly, deeply, and roundly emarginated, with two lateral lobules; each lobule with rounded apex (
<figureCitation box="[319,410,1977,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Melaneremus? bellus sp. nov.: head and pronotum in dorsal view (A); face in anterior view (B); anterior half of body in lateral view (C); stridulatory files on abdominal tergite (D); female abdominal apex in posterior view (E); ovipositor in lateral view (F); female subgenital plate in ventral view (G); male abdominal apex in dorsal view (H); and male abdominal apex in ventral view (I). Scale bars: 5 mm (C, F); 2 mm (A, B, H); 1 mm (D, E, G, I)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441903/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="585">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
). Posterior part of subgenital plate circa 2.3 times wider than long, broadly triangular, with apex subacute (
<figureCitation box="[320,408,2010,2035]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Melaneremus? bellus sp. nov.: head and pronotum in dorsal view (A); face in anterior view (B); anterior half of body in lateral view (C); stridulatory files on abdominal tergite (D); female abdominal apex in posterior view (E); ovipositor in lateral view (F); female subgenital plate in ventral view (G); male abdominal apex in dorsal view (H); and male abdominal apex in ventral view (I). Scale bars: 5 mm (C, F); 2 mm (A, B, H); 1 mm (D, E, G, I)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441903/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="585">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor long and feebly curved; margins smooth, with subobtuse apex (
<figureCitation box="[1243,1327,2010,2035]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[170,1440,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Melaneremus? bellus sp. nov.: head and pronotum in dorsal view (A); face in anterior view (B); anterior half of body in lateral view (C); stridulatory files on abdominal tergite (D); female abdominal apex in posterior view (E); ovipositor in lateral view (F); female subgenital plate in ventral view (G); male abdominal apex in dorsal view (H); and male abdominal apex in ventral view (I). Scale bars: 5 mm (C, F); 2 mm (A, B, H); 1 mm (D, E, G, I)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441903/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="585">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441903/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="586" startId="7.[151,250,1917,1939]" targetBox="[170,1440,193,1890]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1430,1917,2039]" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1917,1939]" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[281,497,1917,1939]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Karny" authorityYear="1937" box="[281,421,1917,1939]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllacrididae" genus="Melaneremus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Melaneremus</taxonomicName>
? bellus
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[503,584,1918,1939]" pageId="7" pageNumber="586">sp. nov.</emphasis>
: head and pronotum in dorsal view (A); face in anterior view (B); anterior half of body in lateral view (C); stridulatory files on abdominal tergite (D); female abdominal apex in posterior view (E); ovipositor in lateral view (F); female subgenital plate in ventral view (G); male abdominal apex in dorsal view (H); and male abdominal apex in ventral view (I). Scale bars: 5 mm (C, F); 2 mm (A, B, H); 1 mm (D, E, G, I).
</paragraph>
